    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-22T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8921</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-22T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4706, For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 144. <persName>Stetson</persName>. Embassy’s 4093, June 5, 6 p.m. Your 154.
                    On April 30 [<hi rend="italic">29</hi>] War Trade Board passed resolution
                    providing that upon similar action being taken by the Governments of Great
                    Britain, France, and Italy committees may be constituted consisting of
                    representatives of each of above countries and the United States at Paris,
                    London, and Washington to recommend action to be taken upon all applications for
                    licenses to trade with enemy other than certain excepted classes. Committee in
                    Paris to handle transactions with persons in Spain, Morocco, and Switzerland.
                    Committee in London to handle transactions with persons in northern neutral
                    countries. Committee in Washington to handle transactions with persons resident
                    in Western Hemisphere. Now awaiting final approval of Great Britain to put plan
                    in operation. This has not been received in Washington as yet. When received,
                    full particulars, including instructions as to your course of action, will be
                    sent you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
